<span class="pl-kos">}</span></pre></div>
<p dir="auto">Here's what I propose. We (and by that I mean <a class="user-mention notranslate" data-hovercard-type="user" data-hovercard-url="/users/jrburke/hovercard" data-octo-click="hovercard-link-click" data-octo-dimensions="link_type:self" href="https://github.com/jrburke">@jrburke</a>) define a new piece of the <a href="https://github.com/amdjs/amdjs-api/wiki/AMD#defineamd-property-"><code class="notranslate">define.amd</code> spec</a> that says something like this:</p>
<i>
An example of how `define.amd` may be defined for an implementation that <b>does not modify the global namespace</b>:</i>
<div class="snippet-clipboard-content notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="define.amd = {
    noconflict: true
};"><pre class="notranslate"><code class="notranslate">define.amd = {
    noconflict: true
};
</code></pre></div>
<p dir="auto">Then change the pulverizing conditions to something like this:</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-js notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="if ( typeof window === &quot;object&quot; &amp;&amp; typeof window.document === &quot;object&quot; &amp;&amp; !define.amd.noconflict ) {
